OL,3,CWhat is the two-child benefit cap and
OL,4,Chow many kids does it impact?
OL,6,FEstimates suggest that scrapping the
OL,7,Fcap could lift 350,000 children out of
OL,8,Fpoverty and reduce the depth of
OL,9,Fpoverty for a further 800,000 children.
OL,11,FAccording to the Institute for Fiscal
OL,12,FStudies (IFS), families with three
OL,13,Fchildren receiving benefits for the
OL,14,Ffirst two lose out on an average of
OL,15,F#3,455 a year.
OL,17,FA child is said to be living in
OL,18,Fpoverty if they live in a household
OL,19,Fwith an income below 60% of the
OL,20,Fnational median income.
