OL,3,CWhat is the two-child benefit cap and
OL,4,Chow many kids does it impact?
OL,6,FThere is concern that the overall cap
OL,7,Fwill mean that many families remain in
OL,8,Fpoverty even if the two-child limit is
OL,9,Flifted, as the extra money they would
OL,10,Fget for their third or fourth child
OL,11,Fwill push them above the overall limit.
OL,13,FThe Institute for Fiscal Studies
OL,14,Festimates there would be around 70,000
OL,15,Fof the poorest households pushed above
OL,16,Fthe overall benefit cap, meaning the
OL,17,Fgains from reversing the two-child
OL,18,Flimit would be fully or partially
OL,19,Fwiped out.
